, within the upper limits of dust production from a sample stacked image of\n1998 KY$_{26}$ of $\\dot{M}_{\\rm Dust}<0.2$ g s$^{-1}$. This production\ncorresponds to brightness variations of order $\\sim0.0025\\%$, which are\nundetectable in extant photometric data. We assess the future observability of\neach of these targets, and find that the orbit of 1998 KY$_{26}$ -- which is\nalso the target for the extended Hayabusa2 mission -- exhibits favorable\nviewing geometry before 2025.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 15 Dec 2022 20:00:53 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 17 Jan 2023 15:58:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-01-18"}
